title: For Sale:  Remington 700 Classic Limited Edition 7x57 Mauser
postcontent: In 1981 Remington started the "Limited Edition" series of the 700 Classic line by releasing a limited number of rifles in classic calibers. They made these rifles for 25 yrs in a different caliber each year. The first year they made the rifle in the legendary 7x57mm Mauser, They only made a  few more than 2,000 for this introductory year. Not only did this rifle survive but it is in very close to perfect condition. The rifle is so nice that I only take it out of the safe to show it off. I have never hunted with it. It should be treated like the rare "classic" that it is. It has leupold rings and bases and a nice vintage Weaver K4 scope, which looks appropriate on this rifle. If you collect the LE series of 700's you know it starts with this one. I will ship this rifle at buyers expense. I will email or text you better pictures upon request.
